Articles.Content:
Hello guys, I'll be straightforward ...
The game console is full of notices of missing or invalid things but nothing I do works.
I have a copy of the KSP only for mods, the Steam version only had module manager installed with CKAN.
Yes, my game has 2 DLC's.
Yes, after removing it from Steam I checked if there was any folder left (as far as I know ... no).

MENU SCREEN MESSAGES:
Warning: HighlightiningSystem: Edge Highlightning requires AA to work!

Warning: File 'D: / STEAM / steamapps / common / KerbalSpaceProgram / KSP_X64_Data /../ Missions / MissionScoreInfo.cfg' does not exist

KSC SCREEN MESSAGES:

Warning: Contract Log: ContractDefs prebuilt craft at D: / STEAM / steamapps / common / KerbalSpaceProgram / KSP_x64_Data /../ GameData / Squad / Contracts / PreBuiltCraft / RoverContract / Contract Rover 1a.craft invalid.

I believe it may be a flaw in the version (guess).
I reported this with more details and photos on Squad BugTracker but as I don't know if I can put a link to it here I leave the code:

Squad BugTracker
Bug # 27578 - KallangoVerde1

6 hours ago, KallangoVerde said:

Warning: HighlightiningSystem: Edge Highlightning requires AA to work!

I get this a lot in different scenes. Presumably AA refers to anti-aliasing so changing that setting may get rid of it but why should we?

6 hours ago, KallangoVerde said:

Warning: File 'D: / STEAM / steamapps / common / KerbalSpaceProgram / KSP_X64_Data /../ Missions / MissionScoreInfo.cfg' does not exist

Never seen this but got rid of missions part of MH straight away (assuming it’s from mission builder).

6 hours ago, KallangoVerde said:

KSP_x64_Data /../ GameData / Squad / Contracts / PreBuiltCraft / RoverContract / Contract Rover 1a.craft invalid.

Not seen this specifically but it’s possible to edit the contract cfgs to change the vessel specs to correct if you wanted. It won’t break the game as it is because the contract shouldn’t be generated from my experience (of similar).

On 28/04/2021 at 06:27, FruitGoose said:

Eu percebo muito isso em diferentes cenas. Presumivelmente, AA se refere ao anti-aliasing, portanto, alterar essa configuração pode eliminá-lo, mas por que deveríamos?

I managed to make that message go away.

 

On 28/04/2021 at 06:27, FruitGoose said:

Nunca vi isso, mas me livrei das missões que faziam parte de MH imediatamente (presumindo que fosse do construtor de missões).

Like this? If I do that will the Stock missions disappear?

13 minutes ago, KallangoVerde said:

Like this? If I do that will the Stock missions disappear?

I’m not 100% to be honest as I’ve never played them but it would make sense that they would.

Actually looking at it again, it might just keep your scores for missions (unless it’s a music score but don’t think so) so is probably harmless just to leave as is especially if you play the stock missions and there’s a chance they might be lost. If they’re working as expected I would just ignore the message.
